  <summary>1/29/1987--Introduced.
Agricultural Emergency Assistance Act of 1987 - Makes the 1987 wheat crop eligible for disaster assistance under P.L. 99-500 and P.L. 99-591. Requires disaster claims to be filed by February 28, 1987. Amends the Rural Electrification Act of 1936 to increase the amount of permitted principal prepayment on Rural Electrification Administration loans. Permits the transfer of such funds to the Commodity Credit Corporation for disaster payment use. Requires the Secretary of Agriculture to report to the appropriate congressional committees regarding disaster compensation based on quality loss.</summary>
